Anthrax - Kazakhstan
--------------------
Information received on [and dated] 23 Jun 2016 from Dr Samat Tyulegenov, Director General, RSE "National Reference Center for Veterinary", Ministry of Agriculture, ASTANA, Kazakhstan

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 19 Jun 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 21 Jun 2016
Report date: 23 Jun 2016
Date submitted to OIE: 23 Jun 2016
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Erkindik village, [Shet district], Karaganda
Date of start of the outbreak: 19 Jun 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1831 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Equidae / 900 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep / goats / 269 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.05 / 0.05 / 100 / 0.05
Equidae / 0 / 0 / - / 0
Sheep/goats / 0 / 0 / - / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: vaccination of all susceptible animals was carried out.

Control measures
Measures applied:
Movement control inside the country
- Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)
Administrative division: Karaganda
Species / Total Vaccinated
Cattle / 1830
Equidae / 900
Sheep / goats / 269
- Disinfection/disinfestation
- Quarantine
- Zoning
- No treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Republican State Enterprise, Republican Veterinary Laboratory (regional laboratory) / Cattle / bacteriological examination / 21 Jun 2016 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

