******
[2]
Date: Fri 24 Jun 2016
Source: Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty [edited]
http://www.rferl.org/content/kazakhstan-anthrax-second-outbreak-week/27817577.html


Kazakh authorities say an outbreak of anthrax has been confirmed in the eastern part of the country -- the 2nd outbreak to infect villagers in Kazakhstan within a week. Kazakh Health Minister Tamara Duisenova said on [24 Jun 2016] that 2 residents in village of Kolbatau, in East Kazakhstan Oblast, have tested anthrax positive.

Officials confirmed on [22 Jun 2016] that 2 villagers in Kazakhstan's central region of Karaghandy [Karaganda] had died from anthrax infections, and that 6 people were hospitalized with the deadly disease.

Duisenova on [24 Jun 2016] said 7 people had been diagnosed with anthrax and were being treated at Karaghandy's city hospital.

--
