******
[4]
Date: Fri 24 Jun 2016 16:04
Source: KazTag The Kazakh Telegraph Agency [edited]
http://www.kaztag.kz/en/news/detail.php?ID=469735


Two inhabitants of the East Kazakhstan region have been diagnosed with anthrax, said Tamara Duisenova, Minister of Health Care & Sicial Development. " ... 2 patients -- diagnosis confirmed. All the people are in stable condition. They are getting medical aid," she said.

As for the situation in Karaganda region, she said the yards in Yerkindik [Erkindik] village have been fully checked. 62 people had been in contact with the sick people. "The condition of the 7 hospitalized people is stable, they are getting treatment," she said.

Commenting on the message about the deceased man in Yerkindik village, he applied for medical aid too late. "The man came to hospital and said about a cut, there was no information about anthrax. The main problem is late application for medical aid; secondly, the medical organization had no information that the man had cut his hand in the time of butchering. We have sent the inspection there. The actions of the hospital will be checked," she said.

