[Maps of Kazakhstan can be seen at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regions_of_Kazakhstan and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4307617,56.
To find Zharma in east Kazakhstan, go to http://www.fallingrain.com/world/KZ/15/Zharma.html.

Cutaneous anthrax carries a lethality risk of 10 percent without antibiotic treatment. A characteristic of this lesion, before the black ulcer develops, is that the inflamed area is without pain but it itches and has small vesicles; the draining lymph nodes will be inflamed. Though anthrax is not unknown in eastern Kazakhstan -- outbreaks occurred there in 2008 and 2011 -- if the medical team at Zharma had not seen such a lesion before, they will miss the characteristic itching. - Mod.MHJ]
